AlaVrTrackId.name: AlaVrTrackId
AlaVrTrackId.description: A number that serves to uniquely identify a tracking policy.

AlaVrGroupId.name: AlaVrGroupId
AlaVrGroupId.description: A number that serves to uniquely identify a virtual router group.

alaVRRPStartDelay.name: alaVRRPStartDelay
alaVRRPStartDelay.description: Once VRRP's initial configuration is complete at startup, this object specifies the number of seconds VRRP will delay before leaving the initialize state. This delay is to allow external protocols (spanning tree, OSPF, etc.) time to converge so that when a VRRP virtual router becomes master it will be able to forward traffic.

alaVrrpBfdStatus.name: alaVrrpBfdStatus
alaVrrpBfdStatus.description: Enable or disable the BFD for VRRP.

alaVRRPDefaultInterval.name: alaVRRPDefaultInterval
alaVRRPDefaultInterval.description: The VRRP Router default time interval, in seconds, between sending advertisement messages.

alaVRRPDefaultPriority.name: alaVRRPDefaultPriority
alaVRRPDefaultPriority.description: This object specifies the VRRP Router default priority to be used for the virtual router master election process. Higher values imply higher priority.

alaVRRPDefaultPreemptMode.name: alaVRRPDefaultPreemptMode
alaVRRPDefaultPreemptMode.description: The VRRP Router default preempt mode. Controls whether a higher priority virtual router will preempt a lower priority master.

alaVRRPAdminState.name: alaVRRPAdminState
alaVRRPAdminState.description: This object is used to force a change in to the vrrpOperAdminState of virtual routers in the vrrpOperTable. Setting a value of allEnable will cause the vrrpOperAdminState of each entry in the table to be set to up. Setting a value of enable will set the vrrpOperAdminState to up but only for the set of virtual routers whose vrrpOperAdminState was down by default (as occurs when the virtual router instance is created) or due to a previous set command of the alaVRRPAdminState to disable. Setting a value of disable will cause the vrrpOperAdminState of each entry in the table to be set to down. This object is of little value when read but will return the last value to which it was set.

alaVRRPSetParam.name: alaVRRPSetParam
alaVRRPSetParam.description: This object is used to force the virtual routers in the vrrpOperTable to revert to the default parameter values specified in alaVRRPDefaultInterval, alaVRRPDefaultPriority, and alaVRRPDefaultPreemptMode. Unless alaVRRPOverride is set to true only virtual routers previously configured with default parameter values are modified. Parameters can be modified individually with the interval, priority, and preempt values, or collectively with the all value. This object is of little value when read but will return the last value to which it was set.

alaVRRPOverride.name: alaVRRPOverride
alaVRRPOverride.description: This object is used in combination with the alaVRRPSetParam object to force all virtual routers in the vrrpOperTable to revert to the default values specified in alaVRRPDefaultInterval, alaVRRPDefaultPriority, and alaVRRPDefaultPreemptMode. This object is of little value when read but will return the last value to which it was set.

alaVrrpTrackTable.name: alaVrrpTrackTable
alaVrrpTrackTable.description: VRRP Tracking Policy table, which consists of a sequence (i.e., one or more conceptual rows) of 'vrrpTrackEntry' items.

alaVrrpTrackEntry.name: alaVrrpTrackEntry
alaVrrpTrackEntry.description: An entry in the vrrpTrackTable containing the operational characteristics of a VRRP tracking policy. Rows in the table cannot be modified unless the value of `vrrpTrackAdminState' is `disabled'.

alaVrrpTrackId.name: alaVrrpTrackId
alaVrrpTrackId.description: This object contains the Tracking Policy Identifier (TRACKID).

alaVrrpTrackState.name: alaVrrpTrackState
alaVrrpTrackState.description: The conditional state of the tracking policy entity.

alaVrrpTrackAdminState.name: alaVrrpTrackAdminState
alaVrrpTrackAdminState.description: This object will enable/disable the tracking policy function.

alaVrrpTrackEntityType.name: alaVrrpTrackEntityType
alaVrrpTrackEntityType.description: This object specifies the tracking policy entity type currently in use.

alaVrrpTrackEntityPort.name: alaVrrpTrackEntityPort
alaVrrpTrackEntityPort.description: This object contains the Tracking Policy Entity. A port ifIndex or 0 if not significant. The alaVrrpTrackEntityPort, alaVrrpTrackEntityInterface, alaVrrpTrackEntityIpv6Interface, and alaVrrpTrackEntityIpAddr are mutually exclusive of one another. The last one set is the valid one and identifies the entity type.

alaVrrpTrackPriority.name: alaVrrpTrackPriority
alaVrrpTrackPriority.description: This object specifies the value by which the priority of virtual routers associated with the tracking policy will be decremented when the tracked entity's operational state transitions from up to down, or will be incremented when the tracked entity's operational state transitions from down to up.

alaVrrpTrackRowStatus.name: alaVrrpTrackRowStatus
alaVrrpTrackRowStatus.description: The row status variable, used in accordance to installation and removal conventions for conceptual rows. To create a row in this table, a manager sets this object to either createAndGo(4) or createAndWait(5). Until instances of all corresponding columns are appropriately configured, the value of the corresponding instance of the `vrrpTrackRowStatus' column will be read as notReady(3). In particular, a newly created row cannot be made active(1) until (minimally) the corresponding instances of `vrrpTrackId', and either one of : alaVrrpTrackEntityPort, or alaVrrpTrackEntityInterface have been set.

alaVrrpTrackEntityInterface.name: alaVrrpTrackEntityInterface
alaVrrpTrackEntityInterface.description: This object contains the Tracking Policy Entity. An interface. The alaVrrpTrackEntityPort, alaVrrpTrackEntityInterface, alaVrrpTrackEntityIpv6Interface, and alaVrrpTrackEntityIpAddr are mutually exclusive of one another. The last one set is the valid one and identifies the entity type.

alaVrrpTrackEntityIpv6Interface.name: alaVrrpTrackEntityIpv6Interface
alaVrrpTrackEntityIpv6Interface.description: This object contains the Tracking Policy Entity. An Ipv6 interface. The alaVrrpTrackEntityPort, alaVrrpTrackEntityInterface, alaVrrpTrackEntityIpv6Interface, and alaVrrpTrackEntityIpAddr are mutually exclusive of one another. The last one set is the valid one and identifies the entity type.

alaVrrpTrackEntityIpAddrType.name: alaVrrpTrackEntityIpAddrType
alaVrrpTrackEntityIpAddrType.description: This object contains the Tracking Policy Entity IP Address type.

alaVrrpTrackEntityIpAddr.name: alaVrrpTrackEntityIpAddr
alaVrrpTrackEntityIpAddr.description: This object contains the Tracking Policy Entity. An IPv4 for or IPv6 Address based on alaVrrpTrackEntityIpAddrType. The alaVrrpTrackEntityPort, alaVrrpTrackEntityInterface, alaVrrpTrackEntityIpv6Interface, and alaVrrpTrackEntityIpAddr are mutually exclusive of one another. The last one set is the valid one and identifies the entity type.

alaVrrpTrackBfdStatus.name: alaVrrpTrackBfdStatus
alaVrrpTrackBfdStatus.description: Enables BFD for a VRRP track.

alaVrrpAssoTrackTable.name: alaVrrpAssoTrackTable
alaVrrpAssoTrackTable.description: The table of tracking policies associated with this virtual router.

alaVrrpAssoTrackEntry.name: alaVrrpAssoTrackEntry
alaVrrpAssoTrackEntry.description: An entry in the table contains a tracking policy id that is associated with a virtual router. The number of rows for a given ifIndex and VrId will equal the number of tracking policies associated with the virtual router (equivalent to alaVrrpTrackCount'). Rows in the table cannot be modified unless the value of `vrrpOperAdminState' is `disabled' and the 'vrrpOperState' has transitioned to `initialize'.

alaVrrpAssoTrackId.name: alaVrrpAssoTrackId
alaVrrpAssoTrackId.description: The identifier of the tracking policy the virtual router is responsible for monitoring.

alaVrrpAssoTrackRowStatus.name: alaVrrpAssoTrackRowStatus
alaVrrpAssoTrackRowStatus.description: The row status variable, used according to installation and removal conventions for conceptual rows. Setting this object to active(1) or createAndGo(4) results in the addition of an associated tracking policy for a virtual router. Destroying the entry or setting it to notInService(2) removes the associated tracking policy from the virtual router. The use of other values is implementation-dependent.

alaVrrpGroupTable.name: alaVrrpGroupTable
alaVrrpGroupTable.description: VRRP Group table, which consists of a sequence (i.e., one or more conceptual rows) of 'vrrpGroupEntry' items.

alaVrrpGroupEntry.name: alaVrrpGroupEntry
alaVrrpGroupEntry.description: An entry in the vrrpGroupTable containing the characteristics of a VRRP group.

alaVrrpGroupId.name: alaVrrpGroupId
alaVrrpGroupId.description: This object contains the Tracking Policy Identifier (GROUPID).

alaVrrpGroupInterval.name: alaVrrpGroupInterval
alaVrrpGroupInterval.description: The VRRP Group time interval, in seconds, between sending advertisement messages.

alaVrrpGroupPriority.name: alaVrrpGroupPriority
alaVrrpGroupPriority.description: This object specifies the VRRP Group priority to be used for the virtual router master election process. Higher values imply higher priority.

alaVrrpGroupPreemptMode.name: alaVrrpGroupPreemptMode
alaVrrpGroupPreemptMode.description: The VRRP Group preempt mode. Controls whether a higher priority virtual router will preempt a lower priority master.

alaVrrpGroupAdminState.name: alaVrrpGroupAdminState
alaVrrpGroupAdminState.description: This object is used to force a change in to the vrrpOperAdminState of virtual routers in the corresponding alaVRRPAssoGroupTable entry. Setting a value of allEnable will cause the vrrpOperAdminState of each vrrpOperEntry to be set to up. Setting a value of enable will set the vrrpOperAdminState to up but only for the set of virtual routers in the group whose vrrpOperAdminState was down by default (as occurs when the virtual router instance is created) or due to a previous set command of the alaVrrpGroupAdminState or alaVRRPAdminState to disable. Setting a value of disable will cause the vrrpOperAdminState of each entry in the table to be set to down. This object is of little value when read but will return the last value to which it was set.

alaVrrpGroupSetParam.name: alaVrrpGroupSetParam
alaVrrpGroupSetParam.description: This object is used to force the virtual routers in the corresponding alaVRRPAssoGroupTable to revert to the group parameter values specified in alaVrrpGroupInterval, alaVrrpGroupPriority, and alaVrrpGroupPreemptMode. Unless alaVrrpGroupOverride is set to true only virtual routers previously configured with default or group parameter values are modified. Parameters can be modified individually with the interval, priority, and preempt values, or collectively with the all value. This object is of little value when read but will return the last value to which it was set.

alaVrrpGroupOverride.name: alaVrrpGroupOverride
alaVrrpGroupOverride.description: This object is used in combination with the alaVrrpGroupSetParam object to force all virtual routers in the corresponding alaVrrpAssoGroupTable to revert to the group parameter values specified in alaVrrpGroupInterval, alaVrrpGroupPriority, and alaVrrpGroupPreemptMode. This object is of little value when read but will return the last value to which it was set.

alaVrrpGroupRowStatus.name: alaVrrpGroupRowStatus
alaVrrpGroupRowStatus.description: The row status variable, used in accordance to installation and removal conventions for conceptual rows. To create a row in this table, a manager sets this object to either createAndGo(4) or createAndWait(5). Until instances of all corresponding columns are appropriately configured, the value of the corresponding instance of the `alaVrrpGroupRowStatus' column will be read as notReady(3). In particular, a newly created row cannot be made active(1) until (minimally) the corresponding instance of `alaVrrpGroupId' has been set.

alaVrrpAssoGroupTable.name: alaVrrpAssoGroupTable
alaVrrpAssoGroupTable.description: The table of virtual routers associated with this group.

alaVrrpAssoGroupEntry.name: alaVrrpAssoGroupEntry
alaVrrpAssoGroupEntry.description: An entry in the table contains a virtual router id that is associated with a virtual router group.

alaVrrpAssoGroupRowStatus.name: alaVrrpAssoGroupRowStatus
alaVrrpAssoGroupRowStatus.description: The row status variable, used according to installation and removal conventions for conceptual rows. Setting this object to active(1) or createAndGo(4) results in the addition of an associated virtual router for a group. Destroying the entry or setting it to notInService(2) removes the associated virtual router from the group. The use of other values is implementation-dependent.

alaVrrpOperTable.name: alaVrrpOperTable
alaVrrpOperTable.description: Table of virtual router configuration info.

alaVrrpOperEntry.name: alaVrrpOperEntry
alaVrrpOperEntry.description: An entry in the table, config information about a given virtual router.

alaVrrpCurrentPriority.name: alaVrrpCurrentPriority
alaVrrpCurrentPriority.description: This object specifies the priority currently used for the virtual router master election process. Higher values imply higher priority. A priority of '0', although not settable, is sent by the master router to indicate that this router has ceased to participate in VRRP and a backup virtual router should transition to become a new master. A priority of 255 is used for the router that owns the associated IP address(es).

alaVrrpTrackCount.name: alaVrrpTrackCount
alaVrrpTrackCount.description: The number of tracking policies associated with a virtual router.

alaVrrpGroupIdent.name: alaVrrpGroupIdent
alaVrrpGroupIdent.description: The VRRP group to which this virtual router belongs. A value of zero indicates that the virtual router is not affiliated with any group.

alaVrrp3AssoTrackTable.name: alaVrrp3AssoTrackTable
alaVrrp3AssoTrackTable.description: The table of tracking policies associated with this virtual router.

alaVrrp3AssoTrackEntry.name: alaVrrp3AssoTrackEntry
alaVrrp3AssoTrackEntry.description: An entry in the table contains a tracking policy id that is associated with a virtual router. The number of rows for a given IP Version, VrId, and ifIndex will equal the number of tracking policies associated with the virtual router (equivalent to alaVrrp3TrackCount'). Rows in the table cannot be modified unless the value of `alaVrrp3OperAdminState' is `disabled' and the 'alaVrrp3OperState' has transitioned to `initialize'.

alaVrrp3AssoTrackId.name: alaVrrp3AssoTrackId
alaVrrp3AssoTrackId.description: The identifier of the tracking policy the virtual router is responsible for monitoring.

alaVrrp3AssoTrackRowStatus.name: alaVrrp3AssoTrackRowStatus
alaVrrp3AssoTrackRowStatus.description: The row status variable, used according to installation and removal conventions for conceptual rows. Setting this object to active(1) or createAndGo(4) results in the addition of an associated tracking policy for a virtual router. Destroying the entry or setting it to notInService(2) removes the associated tracking policy from the virtual router. The use of other values is implementation-dependent.

alaVrrp3OperExTable.name: alaVrrp3OperExTable
alaVrrp3OperExTable.description: Table of virtual router configuration info.

alaVrrp3OperExEntry.name: alaVrrp3OperExEntry
alaVrrp3OperExEntry.description: An entry in the table, config information about a given virtual router.

alaVrrp3CurrentPriority.name: alaVrrp3CurrentPriority
alaVrrp3CurrentPriority.description: This object specifies the priority currently used for the virtual router master election process. Higher values imply higher priority. A priority of '0', although not settable, is sent by the master router to indicate that this router has ceased to participate in VRRP and a backup virtual router should transition to become a new master. A priority of 255 is used for the router that owns the associated IP address(es).

alaVrrp3TrackCount.name: alaVrrp3TrackCount
alaVrrp3TrackCount.description: The number of tracking policies associated with a virtual router.

alaVrrp3GroupIdent.name: alaVrrp3GroupIdent
alaVrrp3GroupIdent.description: The VRRP group to which this virtual router belongs. A value of zero indicates that the virtual router is not affiliated with any group.

alaVRRPCompliance.name: alaVRRPCompliance
alaVRRPCompliance.description: The compliance statement for switches with Alcatel VRRP and implementing ALCATEL-IND1-VRRP-MIB.

alaVRRPConfigGroup.name: alaVRRPConfigGroup
alaVRRPConfigGroup.description: A collection of objects to support management of Alcatel VRRP.

alaVRRPv2ConfigGroup.name: alaVRRPv2ConfigGroup
alaVRRPv2ConfigGroup.description: A collection of objects to support management of Alcatel VRRP

alaVrrp3AssoTrackTableGroup.description: The table of tracking policies associated with this virtual router.

alaVrrp3OperExEntryGroup.description: Table of virtual router configuration info.
